      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "6101740936c26b8083db92c49c5eca8a7fcf31fb",
            "subject": "LU-56 libcfs: CPT affinity workitem scheduler"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-05-16 06:53:43.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-27 16:43:15.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-56 lnet: SMP improvements for LNet selftest",
        "message": "LU-56 lnet: SMP improvements for LNet selftest\n\nLNet selftest is using a global WI threads pool to handle all RPCs,\nit has performance problem on fat cores machine because all threads\nwill contend on global queues protected by a single spinlock.\nThis patch will fix this by creating WI scheduler for each CPT,\nRPCs will be dispatched to WI schedulers on different CPTs, and there\nis no contention between threads in different WI schedulers.\n\nAnother major change in this patch is create percpt data for LST\nservice. In current implementation each service has a global data\nstructure to store buffer list and RPC list etch, and all operations\non them are protected by per-service lock, again, this could be a\nserious performance issue if the service is busy enough. Having\npercpt service data would resolve this issue because threads running\nin one CPT will only require lock lock and access local data.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I8035faf2e87d8e424a8c2fac903bf3b241668e00\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
